The unions want the National Treasury to unconditionally release all monies owed by the counties to enable them meet their financial obligations.The striking workers also want President Uhuru Kenyatta to provide leadership and unlock the standoff. Striking Mombasa County health workers have issued new demands before they end their strike.
The Kenya National Union of Nurses (KNUN), Kenya Union of Clinical officers Union, Kenya National Union of Medical Laboratory officers and Kenya Health Professional Society, representing more than 2,000 health care workers, accused the county government of being irresponsible and ignorant.



